https://leetcode.com/problems/find-peak-element/description/

QUESTION:
Example 1:
Input: nums = [1,2,3,1]
Output: 2
Example 2:
Input: nums = [1,2,1,3,5,6,4]
Output: 5

SOLUTION:
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(logn)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(1)
1)find the mid value
2)check if mid-1 and mid+1 is less than mid then return mid(that is index value)
3)if not if mid<mid+1 then it means left side is greater so high=mid
4)else right side is greater so low=mid+1;



CODE:
class Solution {
    public int findPeakElement(int[] nums) {
        int low=0;
        int high=nums.length-1;
        while(low<=high){
            int mid=low+(high-low)/2;
            if((mid==0 ||nums[mid]>nums[mid-1]) && (mid==nums.length-1 || nums[mid]>nums[mid+1]))return mid;
            else if(nums[mid]>nums[mid+1])high=mid;
            else low=mid+1;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
